@NODE "Introduction" "Strings Module"
@{b}
                              STRINGS MODULE
@{ub}


The  strings module handles various string functions that are common to all
programming  languages  and  operating  systems.  This includes support for
string comparisons, conversions, searching, copying etc.

This  module supports strings of an unlimited length, so you do not need to
worry  about any possible limitations.  As a bonus, this means that you can
also  use  the  string functions on large text files and documents (so long
as you null terminate them).

The  most  important  thing  to remember is that some functions will return
strings  that have had their space allocated with AllocMemBlock().  If this
is the case for a function you are using, make sure you call FreeMemBlock()
on the resulting string before your program exits.

@EndNode
