@NODE "IntToStr()" "Strings: IntToStr()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     IntToStr()
Short:    Converts an integer to a string.
Synopsis: BYTE * IntToStr(LONG Integer [d0], BYTE *String [a0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  converts  an  integer  to a string.  The String argument is
optional,  if  you  leave  it  as NULL then this function will allocate the
string for you with AllocMemBlock() at defaults of MEM_DATA|MEM_PRIVATE.

If  the  Integer  is  negative,  this function will place a '-' sign at the
front of the resulting string.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Integer
  The integer that you want to convert.

String
  Pointer to a string that is at least 12 characters long, or leave this as
  NULL to have this function allocate a string for you.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns a pointer to the beginning of the converted string.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrCapitalize()" "Strings: StrCapitalize()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrCapitalize()
Short:    Capitalizes a string.
Synopsis: void StrCapitalize(BYTE *String [a0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This function will will capitalize a string, so that every word starts with
a  capital letter.  Numbers and other non-alpha characters at the beginning
of any given word will not be affected.  Example:

  "every WOrd starts WITH a 2apital"

  ..becomes..

  "Every Word Starts With A 2apital"

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String
  Pointer to a string that you want to capitalize.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrClone()" "Strings: StrClone()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrClone()
Short:    Returns a memblock that is an exact duplicate of the String.
Synopsis: BYTE * StrClone(BYTE *String [a0], LONG MemFlags [d0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This function allows you to create an exact duplicate of a string.  You can
choose  what  sort of memory the string should be copied to, eg MEM_PRIVATE
or  MEM_PUBLIC  (specify  NULL  for a private default).  When this function
returns  it  will  give  you a standard MemBlock, which you are expected to
free when you are finished with it.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String
  Pointer to the string that you want to duplicate.

MemFlags
  The type of memory that you want for your cloned string.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns  an exact duplicate of the string.  Remember to call FreeMemBlock()
on the resulting string once you are done with it.  If this function fails,
NULL is returned.

@EndNode
