@NODE "StrCompare()" "Strings: StrCompare()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrCompare()
Short:    Compares two strings.
Synopsis: LONG StrCompare(BYTE *String1 [a0], BYTE *String2 [a1],
            LONG Length [d0], WORD CaseSensitive [d1])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Compares  two strings against each other.  Supports case in/sensitivity and
length specifications.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String1, String2
  Pointers to the two strings that you want to compare.

Length
  The maximum amount of characters that you want to compare.  If one
  of the strings is shorter than the specified Length, StrCompare() will
  only compare up to the length of the shortest string.  If you leave the
  Length at NULL, the maximum possible string length will be compared.

CaseSensitive
  Set to TRUE if you want a case sensitive comparison (this is fastest) or
  set to FALSE for case insensitive.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns TRUE if the strings match, otherwise returns FALSE.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrCopy()" "Strings: StrCopy()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrCopy()
Short:    Copies the characters of one string to another.
Synopsis: void StrCopy(BYTE *Source [a0], BYTE *Dest [a1], LONG Length [d0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This function copies part of one string over to another.

If  the  Length is specifed as NULL then this function will copy the entire
source  string  over  to  the  destination.   Note  that  if  this function
encounters  the  end  of the Source string (ie NULL) while copying, then it
will stop automatically to prevent copying of junk characters.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Source
  Pointer to the string that you are copying from.

Dest
  Pointer to the string that you are copying to.

Length
  The maximum number of characters that you want to copy.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrLength()" "Strings: StrLength()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrLength()
Short:    Calculates the length of a string.
Synopsis: LONG StrLength(BYTE *String [a0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This function will calculate the length of a string, not including the null
byte.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String
  Pointer to the string you want to examine.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns the length of the string.

@EndNode
