@NODE "StrLower()" "Strings: StrLower()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrLower()
Short:    Changes a string so that all alpha characters are in lower case.
Synopsis: void StrLower(BYTE *String [a0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  will  alter  a string so that all upper case characters are
changed to lower case.

@{b}@{u}EXAMPLE@{uu}@{ub}

  "HeLLo world"

   ..becomes..

  "hello world"

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String
  Pointer to the string that you want in lower case.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrMerge()" "Strings: StrMerge()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrMerge()
Short:    Merges two strings together.
Synopsis: BYTE * StrMerge(BYTE *String1 [a0], BYTE *String2 [a1],
            BYTE *Dest [a2])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  will  merge  two  strings  together  in order to form a new
string.   You  can  give  this  function a destination to merge the strings
into, or you can have the function allocate a string area for you.

@{b}@{u}EXAMPLE@{uu}@{ub}

  Merge = StrMerge("Hello ","World",NULL);

  ..creates..

  "Hello World"

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String1
  Pointer to the first string.

String2
  Pointer to the second string.

Dest
  The destination for the merge, or NULL if you want a string to be
  allocated for you.  If you have a string allocated, make sure that you
  call FreeMemBlock() on it once you are finished.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns the destination string if successful, otherwise NULL.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrSearch()" "Strings: StrSearch()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrSearch()
Short:    Searches a string for a particular keyword/phrase.
Synopsis: LONG StrSearch(BYTE *Search [a0], BYTE *String [a1])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This function allows you to search for a particular keyword/phrase inside a
string.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Search
  A string that specifies the keyword/phrase you are searching for.

String
  The string that you want to search.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns the byte position of the keyword (byte position starts from 0).  If
the keyword could not be found, this function returns -1.

@EndNode
