@NODE "StrToInt()" "Strings: StrToInt()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrToInt()
Short:    Converts a string to its integer equivalent.
Synopsis: LONG StrToInt(BYTE *String [a0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  converts  a  string to its integer equivalent.  It supports
negative  numbers  (if  a  '-' symbol is leading the first digit) and skips
leading spaces and non-numeric characters that occur before any digits.

If  the function encounters a non-numeric character once it has started its
digit processing, it immediately stops and returns the result calculated up
to that point.

@{b}EXAMPLES@{ub}
This  table  illustrates  what  will  be  returned  for  various  character
combinations:

  String     | Integer
  -----------+--------
  "183"      |  183
  "  2902a6" |  2902
  "hx239"    |  239
  "-45"      |  -45
  " j!f-9"   |  -9


@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String
  Pointer to the string that you want to be converted.

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns the resulting integer.

@EndNode
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@NODE "StrUpper()" "Strings: StrUpper()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StrUpper()
Short:    Changes a string so that all alpha characters are in upper case.
Synopsis: void StrUpper(BYTE *String [a0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This  function  will  alter  a string so that all lower case characters are
changed to upper case.

@{b}@{u}EXAMPLE@{uu}@{ub}

  "HeLLo world"

   ..becomes..

  "HELLO WORD"

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
String
  Pointer to the string that you want in upper case.

@EndNode
